## HTML

- Semantic elements: `<section>`, `<nav>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<main>`, `<article>`, `<button>` — not generic `<div>` for those roles.
- Structure: `.page-container` > `<section class="section-name">` > `.content-wrap`.
- **CTAs:** Use `.act-btn` as the base class on every call-to-action. Add page- or section-specific classes alongside `.act-btn` when overrides are needed in `style.css`. Example:
  ```html
  <a href="..." class="act-btn">Get started</a>
  <a href="..." class="act-btn call-btn">Call me back</a>
  ```
- No inline styles (`style="..."`). No inline event handlers (`onclick`, `onchange`). Use classes and JS files or an inline `<script>` block at the bottom of `<body>`.
- Every `<input>` has an associated `<label>`. All `<img>` have descriptive `alt` text.
- Heading hierarchy: one H1 per page; H2 → H3 in order with no skips.
- Text alignment: section `h2` is **centered by default**. Apply `.t-left` or a section-scoped rule when the section has left-aligned body copy flowing directly beneath the heading.

