## CSS

- Page-specific styles only in `style.css`. Never modify `zohocustom.css` or `product.css`; override in `style.css` if needed.
- **Source files:** Never copy `zohocustom.css` or `product.css` into a page directory. Pages that need Zoho chrome must link to `../source/zohocustom.css` in HTML. Copied files fall out of sync with the source and cause style drift.
- **Font and typography:** Before writing any typography rule (font-size, font-family, line-height, letter-spacing) for h1–h6, `p`, or `a`, check `zohocustom.css` and align with what is defined there. Use `:root` font variables (`--zf-primary-regular`, `--zf-primary-semibold`, `--zf-primary-bold`) and the global body font. Do not introduce arbitrary font values; only override when the design explicitly requires it.
- **`.content-wrap`:** Fully defined in `zohocustom.css`. Do not write any CSS for `.content-wrap` in page styles.
- **`.act-btn`:** Base CTA styles are defined globally. Do not redefine base padding, border-radius, or font on `.act-btn`; only add variant classes (e.g. `.call-btn`, `.book-btn`) in `style.css` for colour or border overrides.
- **Brand CTA red (immutable):** Set `--color-brand-cta: #e42527` and `--primary-btn-color: #e42527` in `:root`. Only `.cta-btn.act-btn` and **See all testimonials** use red — keep each page's own theme for everything else. See `Rulesbook.md` §2.2.1.
- **Testimonial cards (immutable palette):** `.zwc-nav-box` peach/mint/blue pastels are **fixed extracted values** on every page — never derived from page theme. Copy from `Rulesbook.md` §2.2.2 / `team-dna.json`. Gold standard: `output/sales-dashboard-examples/style.css`.
- Single-class selectors preferred; BEM-like naming (`.section-name`, `.section-name__element`). Avoid `!important` unless overriding third-party or base styles.
- Use design tokens / CSS variables where available. Prefer `var(--...)` over hardcoded hex values when tokens exist.

