## Responsive breakpoints

Use all six breakpoints in every page. Desktop-first — apply base styles at full width, then progressively reduce with each breakpoint.

| Breakpoint | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `max-width: 1200px` | Hide sticky nav and sidebar; expand left content to full width |
| `max-width: 1024px` | Stack multi-column layouts (grids and side-by-side cards go to single column); stack feature tabs vertically |
| `max-width: 991px` | Scale typography down (see type scale below); shrink buttons; reduce intro text size |
| `max-width: 768px` | Tighten card and panel padding; stack step lists; reduce number panel widths |
| `max-width: 567px` | Reduce section `padding-top` to 40px; tighten card padding further |
| `max-width: 435px` | Wrap stacked CTA buttons; adjust inline-start margins |

