## Global typography and utilities (apply to every page)

Include the following block at the **top of every page's `style.css`**, before any page-specific styles. Do not invent different values per page.

```css
/* Global typography and utilities — consistent across all pages */
.page-container h2 {
    font-size: 32px;
    line-height: 1.3;
    text-align: center;
    font-family: Zoho_Puvi_Bold;
}

.page-container h3 {
    font-size: 20px;
    line-height: 1.4;
    width: 100%;
}

.page-container p,
.page-container li {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.75;
}

.t-left {
    text-align: left !important;
}

.t-center {
    text-align: center;
}

.d-block {
    display: block;
}

.d-flex {
    display: flex;
}

.d-flex-row {
    flex-direction: row;
}

.d-flex-column {
    flex-direction: column;
}

.align-center {
    align-items: center;
}

.justify-center {
    justify-content: center;
}

.p-90 {
    padding: 90px 0;
}

.p-50 {
    padding: 50px 0;
}

.title-desc {
    font-size: 20px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    width: 100%;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
}

.m-0 {
    margin: 0;
}

.m-t-0 {
    margin-top: 0 !important;
}

.p-b-0 {
    padding-bottom: 0 !important;
}

.m-t-15 {
    margin-top: 15px;
}

.m-b-30 {
    margin-bottom: 30px;
}

.f-20 {
    font-size: 20px;
    line-height: 1.6;
}

.p-t-0 {
    padding-top: 0;
}
```

### Responsive typography scale

Apply these overrides inside your responsive breakpoints — do not set different base values per page:

```css
@media (max-width: 991px) {
    .page-container h2 { font-size: 26px; }
    .page-container h3 { font-size: 18px; }
    .page-container p,
    .page-container li  { font-size: 15px; }
    .f-20, .title-desc  { font-size: 17px; }
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-container h2 { font-size: 22px; }
    .page-container h3 { font-size: 17px; }
}
```

### Usage rules
- **`h2` / `h3`:** Never override font-size in page-specific CSS unless the design explicitly requires it. Use `.t-left` to left-align a section heading; do not write a new selector for `text-align` alone.
- **`.title-desc` and `.f-20`:** Use only for the lead paragraph that directly follows an `h2`. Do not apply to every `<p>` or general body text.
- **Utility classes:** Use the classes above for layout and spacing instead of writing new single-property rules.

