## Spacing system

Use these values consistently across all sections and components. Do not introduce arbitrary padding, margin, or gap values.

| Property | Desktop | ≤ 768px | ≤ 567px |
|---|---|---|---|
| Section `padding-top` | `65px` | `65px` | `40px` |
| Card / panel padding | `24px` | `20px` | `16px` |
| Grid / flex `gap` | `20px` | `16px` | `16px` |
| Margin before a grid or list | `28px – 30px` | same | same |
| Step list item `padding` | `20px 0` | `16px 0` | `16px 0` |

---

## UI component patterns

Use these standard patterns for recurring components. Do not build alternative structures for the same component type.

### Vertical tab (feature tabs)

```html
<div class="features-tabs">
  <div class="features-tab-list">
    <button class="features-tab-btn active" data-tab="0">Label</button>
    <button class="features-tab-btn" data-tab="1">Label</button>
  </div>
  <div class="features-tab-panels">
    <div class="features-tab-panel active" data-panel="0">
      <h3>Title</h3>
      <p>Content</p>
    </div>
    <div class="features-tab-panel" data-panel="1">
      <h3>Title</h3>
      <p>Content</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

Tab switching JS (add to `script.js` or inline `<script>`):
```js
document.querySelectorAll('.features-tab-btn').forEach(function (btn) {
    btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
        document.querySelectorAll('.features-tab-btn').forEach(function (b) { b.classList.remove('active'); });
        document.querySelectorAll('.features-tab-panel').forEach(function (p) { p.classList.remove('active'); });
        btn.classList.add('active');
        document.querySelector('.features-tab-panel[data-panel="' + btn.dataset.tab + '"]').classList.add('active');
    });
});
```

### FAQ accordion

```html
<div class="faq-list">
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-question">Question text</button>
    <div class="faq-answer"><p>Answer text</p></div>
  </div>
</div>
```

Accordion JS:
```js
document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(function (item) {
    item.querySelector('.faq-question').addEventListener('click', function () {
        var isOpen = item.classList.contains('open');
        document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(function (i) {
            i.classList.remove('open');
            i.querySelector('.faq-answer').style.maxHeight = null;
        });
        if (!isOpen) {
            item.classList.add('open');
            item.querySelector('.faq-answer').style.maxHeight = item.querySelector('.faq-answer').scrollHeight + 'px';
        }
    });
});
```

### Numbered single-row cards

Use CSS counters — do not add number markup in HTML:

```css
.cards-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
    counter-reset: card-counter;
}

.card-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 88px 1fr;
    grid-template-rows: auto auto;
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: #F8F9FC;
    counter-increment: card-counter;
}

.card-item::before {
    content: "0" counter(card-counter);
    grid-column: 1;
    grid-row: 1 / span 2;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: #64748B;
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 28px;
    font-family: var(--zf-primary-bold);
}

.card-item h3 { grid-column: 2; grid-row: 1; padding: 24px 24px 6px; margin: 0; }
.card-item p  { grid-column: 2; grid-row: 2; padding: 0 24px 24px; margin: 0; }
```

