## JavaScript

- Add `script.js` when the page has interactivity (tabs, accordions, carousels, modals).
- Short, page-specific initialisation (under ~30 lines) may be placed in an inline `<script>` block at the bottom of `<body>`. Larger or reusable logic must go in `script.js`.
- Never use inline event handlers (`onclick`, `onchange`, `onsubmit`). Always use `addEventListener`.
- Use `const`/`let`; never `var`. Load `script.js` at the end of `<body>`.
- Wrap jQuery-dependent code in `$(document).ready()`. Wrap vanilla JS init in `DOMContentLoaded`.

---

## Accessibility & responsiveness

- All interactive controls (buttons, tabs, accordion triggers) must be keyboard-focusable with a visible focus state.
- WCAG AA contrast for all text. Touch targets ≥ 44×44px on mobile.
- No horizontal scroll at any viewport width.
- All images: `max-width: 100%; height: auto;`. All `<img>` have descriptive `alt` text.

